					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the third quarter of 15th century. </p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex.</support>
								<extent>464 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>170</height>
										<width>120</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>110</height>
										<width>70</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>464 folios (+ 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>60 quires: i10 (folios 1-10), ii-xii8 (folios 11-98), xiii6 (folios 99-104), xiv-xv8 (folios 105-120), xvi6 (folios 121-126), xvii4 (folios 127-130), xviii-xxxv8 (folios 131-274), xxxvi6 (folios 275-280), xxxvii-xlii8 (folios 281-328), xliii6 (folios 329-334), xliv-lix8 (folios 335-462), lx2 (folios 463-464). </p>
									<p>Catchwords at the end of the quires, probably added later.</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="20" writtenLines="20">
									<p>Uniform layout. Visible ruling.</p>
									<p>Numerous decorations:  parashah signs decorated with pen-flourishing, initial-word panels with penwork and pen-flourishing, frontispieces with initial-word panels and full floral border, masoretic lists decorated with penwork and full pen-flourished border.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Sefardi square script, third quarter of 15th century, punctuated. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p> Italian inscription, <date calendar="Gregorian">1518 </date> (folio 10v).</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Post-1660. Dark green leather binding, tooled in gold, centrepiece.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'The Pentateuch, Hafṭaroth, and Five Megilloth. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional 27, 167.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
					</physDesc>
